<h3>Development</h3>
<p>
Silk hosts all of it&apos;s source on <a href="http://www.github.com">GitHub</a> using the <a href="http://git-scm.com/">git</a> version control system.
</p>

<p>
The master repository is found: <a href="http://github.com/tedkulp/silk/tree/master">here</a>.  Feel free to clone it as you see fit in order to make changes for yourself.  If you feel a change is worth submitting back to the project, feel free to send a pull request and we&apos;ll take a look.
</p>

<p>
To clone the repository, you can use the command:
<pre>git clone git://github.com/tedkulp/silk.git</pre>
</p>

<br />

<h4>Bug Tracking</h4>
<p>
Silk is using Lighthouse for it's bug tracking.  Feel free to report (or fix) any bugs by looking <a href="http://silk.lighthouseapp.com/projects/25100-silk-framework/overview" title="Lighthouse Bug Tracker">here</a>.
</p>

<h4>IRC</h4>
<p>
The developers are always hanging out in channel #silk on irc.freenode.net.  Most development related conversation happens there, not to mention general chat as well. We promise we won&apos;t bite and (we try to) never flame for asking a question.
</p>
